Based on the search results, here's what I found about Premiere Pro ExtendScript `createMarker` for sequences:

## Creating Markers in Premiere Pro with ExtendScript

### Sequence Markers

To add a marker to the active sequence, you can use `app.project.activeSequence.markers.createMarker(1)` where the parameter is the time position in seconds.(no content)To create a new comment marker, use `var newMark = markers.createMarker(x)`, with x being the placement time in seconds.

### Full Sequence Marker Example

Here's a working example for adding markers to a sequence:
```javascript
var activeSequence = app.project.activeSequence;
if (activeSequence) {
    var markers = activeSequence.markers;
    if (markers) {
        var newCommentMarker = markers.createMarker(12.345);
        newCommentMarker.end = (newCommentMarker.start.seconds + 5.0);
    }
}
```

### Clip/Project Item Markers

For adding markers to project items (clips), you can get markers from a project item and create them:
```javascript
var markers = projectItem.getMarkers();
if (markers) {
    var numMarkers = markers.numMarkers;
    var newMarker = markers.createMarker(12.345);
    var guid = newMarker.guid;
    newMarker.name = 'Marker created by PProPanel.';
    newMarker.comments = 'Here are some comments, inserted by PProPanel.';
    newMarker.end = (newMarker.start.seconds + 5.0);
}
```

### Web Markers

You can also create web markers with links:
```javascript
var newWebMarker = markers.createMarker(14.345);
newWebMarker.name = 'Web marker created by PProPanel.';
newWebMarker.comments = 'Here are some comments, inserted by PProPanel.';
newWebMarker.end = 17.6789;
newWebMarker.setTypeAsWebLink("http://www.adobe.com", "frame target");
```

### Important Notes

The markers collection (accessible via `app.project.activeSequence.markers`) cannot be accessed like a typical array - you can't just use bracket notation `[x]` to access the xth marker.(no content)As of November 2025, Premiere Pro has moved to UXP (Unified Extensibility Platform) for extensibility. ExtendScript-based integrations are still supported through September 2026.

### Resources

The official PProPanel sample from Adobe exercises the Premiere Pro ExtendScript API and can be found at: https://github.com/Adobe-CEP/Samples/tree/master/PProPanel


