# Premiere Pro UXP Plugin Research: Audio Access and Clip Manipulation

## Question 1: Can UXP plugins access and manipulate audio data directly from timeline clips?

### Direct Answer: NO - Raw audio data access is NOT available via UXP or ExtendScript

**You cannot access raw audio samples/waveform data directly from timeline clips using UXP plugins.** You must export audio to a temporary file first if you need to process the actual audio data.

### What IS Available for Audio via UXP:

The UXP API provides these audio-related classes, but they control metadata and effects, NOT raw audio samples:

```typescript
// AudioTrack - control track-level properties
AudioTrack {
    setMute(mute: boolean): Promise<boolean>
    getMediaType(): Promise<Guid>
    isMuted(): Promise<boolean>
    getTrackItems(trackItemType: Constants.TrackItemType, 
        includeEmptyTrackItems: boolean): AudioClipTrackItem[]
}

// AudioClipTrackItem - clip metadata only
AudioClipTrackItem {
    getMatchName(): Promise<string>
    getName(): Promise<string>
    getInPoint(): Promise<TickTime>
    getOutPoint(): Promise<TickTime>
    getComponentChain(): Promise<AudioComponentChain>
}

// AudioComponentChain - audio effects/filters
AudioComponentChain {
    createInsertComponentAction(component: AudioFilterComponent, index: number): Action
    createAppendComponentAction(component: AudioFilterComponent): Action
    createRemoveComponentAction(component: AudioFilterComponent): Action
}
```

### Workaround for Raw Audio Access:

Per Adobe staff confirmation, the only viable approach is:

1. **Export/render the audio** to a file (MP3, WAV, etc.) using an audio-only export preset
2. **Import the rendered file** into your plugin
3. **Process using Web Audio API** or other JavaScript audio libraries

### Export Audio via ExtendScript (still supported until Sept 2026):

```javascript
// Set in/out points to match clip boundaries
var activeSequence = app.project.activeSequence;
activeSequence.setInPoint(clipStartTime);
activeSequence.setOutPoint(clipEndTime);

// Export using an audio-only preset (.epr file)
app.encoder.encodeSequence(
    activeSequence,
    outputPath,
    audioOnlyPresetPath,  // e.g., "AudioOnly_AAC.epr"
    app.encoder.ENCODE_IN_TO_OUT
);
```

### Official Sources:
- [Premiere Pro UXP API Reference](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/ppro_reference/)
- [Adobe Community - Audio Buffer Access Discussion](https://community.adobe.com/t5/premiere-pro-discussions/extract-audio-buffer-from-premiere-to-extend-script-external-object-c-gt-extend-script/td-p/13156187)
- [PProPanel Sample - Export Examples](https://github.com/Adobe-CEP/Samples/blob/master/PProPanel/jsx/PPRO/Premiere.jsx)

---

## Question 2: APIs for Modifying Clip Labels, Colors, and Markers via UXP

### Direct Answer: YES - Full API support exists for labels, colors, and markers

### Color Labels API (UXP)

```typescript
// Available color label indices (0-15)
enum ProjectItemColorLabel {
    VIOLET = 0, IRIS = 1, LAVENDER = 2, CERULEAN = 3,
    FOREST = 4, ROSE = 5, MANGO = 6, PURPLE = 7,
    BLUE = 8, TEAL = 9, MAGENTA = 10, TAN = 11,
    GREEN = 12, BROWN = 13, YELLOW = 14, ORANGE = 15
}

// ProjectItem methods
getColorLabelIndex(): Promise<number>
createSetColorLabelAction(inColorLabelIndex: number): Action
```

**UXP Code Example - Set Color Label:**

```javascript
const { app } = require("premierepro");

async function setClipColorLabel(projectItem, colorIndex) {
    const project = await app.getProject();

    await project.lockedAccess(async () => {
        const action = projectItem.createSetColorLabelAction(colorIndex);

        await project.executeTransaction(
            (compoundAction) => {
                compoundAction.addAction(action);
            },
            "Set Color Label"
        );
    });
}

// Usage: Set to Cerulean (index 3)
setClipColorLabel(myProjectItem, 3);
```

### Markers API (UXP)

```typescript
// Marker types
enum MarkerType { Comment, Chapter, FlvCuePoint, WebLink }

// Marker colors
enum MarkerColor { GREEN, RED, MAGENTA, ORANGE, YELLOW, BLUE, CYAN }

// Markers class methods
Markers {
    getMarkers(filters?: string[]): Marker[]
    createAddMarkerAction(Name: string, markerType?: string, 
        startTime?: TickTime, duration?: TickTime, 
        comments?: string): Action
    createMoveMarkerAction(marker: Marker, tickTime: TickTime): Action
    createRemoveMarkerAction(marker: Marker): Action
}

// Individual Marker methods
Marker {
    createSetNameAction(name: string): Action
    createSetColorByIndexAction(colorIndex: number): Action
    createSetDurationAction(tickTime: TickTime): Action
    createSetTypeAction(markerType: string): Action
    createSetCommentsAction(comments: string): Action
}
```

**UXP Code Example - Add Marker to Sequence:**

```javascript
const { app, Constants } = require("premierepro");

async function addMarkerToSequence(name, timeInTicks, comments) {
    const project = await app.getProject();
    const sequence = await project.getActiveSequence();
    const markers = await app.getMarkers(sequence);

    await project.lockedAccess(async () => {
        const tickTime = { ticks: timeInTicks };
        const duration = { ticks: 0 };

        const addAction = markers.createAddMarkerAction(
            name,           // marker name
            "Comment",      // markerType
            tickTime,       // startTime
            duration,       // duration
            comments        // comments
        );

        await project.executeTransaction(
            (compoundAction) => {
                compoundAction.addAction(addAction);
            },
            "Add Marker"
        );
    });
}
```

**UXP Code Example - Set Marker Color:**

```javascript
async function setMarkerColor(marker, colorIndex) {
    const project = await app.getProject();

    await project.lockedAccess(async () => {
        const action = marker.createSetColorByIndexAction(colorIndex);

        await project.executeTransaction(
            (compoundAction) => {
                compoundAction.addAction(action);
            },
            "Set Marker Color"
        );
    });
}
```

### ExtendScript Examples (Legacy, supported until Sept 2026)

**Set Color Label:**
```javascript
// Get and set color labels on project items
var projectItem = app.project.rootItem.children[0];
var currentLabel = projectItem.getColorLabel();  // returns 0-15
projectItem.setColorLabel(4);  // Set to Cerulean
```

**Add Markers:**
```javascript
// Add marker to active sequence
var activeSequence = app.project.activeSequence;
var markers = activeSequence.markers;
var newMarker = markers.createMarker(12.345);  // time in seconds
newMarker.name = "My Marker";
newMarker.comments = "Description here";
newMarker.end = newMarker.start.seconds + 5.0;  // 5 second duration

// Add marker to project item (clip)
var clipMarkers = projectItem.getMarkers();
var clipMarker = clipMarkers.createMarker(5.0);
clipMarker.name = "Clip Marker";
```

### Important Limitations:

1. **Markers are attached to ProjectItems, not TrackItems**: "In PPro, all markers and metadata associated with trackItems are actually attached to the backing projectItem; it's not possible to have different markers and metadata for each trackItem."

2. **Color labels apply to ProjectItems only**: "One can only change the label color of projectItems; there's no API to do so, for trackItems."

3. **Track items inherit from source**: "trackItems created from a projectItem will not have their label color updated; any new trackItems created from those projectItems will get the updated label."

### Official Sources:
- [Premiere Pro UXP Markers API](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/ppro_reference/classes/markers/)
- [ProjectItem API Reference](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/ppro_reference/classes/projectitem/)
- [ClipProjectItem API Reference](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/ppro_reference/classes/clipprojectitem/)
- [TypeScript Definitions](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/uxp-premiere-pro/blob/main/src/pages/ppro_reference/types.d.ts)
- [UXP Premiere Pro Samples](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/uxp-premiere-pro-samples)
- [ExtendScript Scripting Guide](https://ppro-scripting.docsforadobe.dev/)
- [PProPanel Sample Code](https://github.com/Adobe-CEP/Samples/blob/master/PProPanel/jsx/PPRO/Premiere.jsx)

---

## Summary Table

| Capability | UXP Support | ExtendScript Support | Notes |
|------------|-------------|---------------------|-------|
| Raw audio sample access | NO | NO | Requires C++ SDK or export-then-process |
| Audio track mute/properties | YES | YES | |
| Audio effects/filters | YES | YES | Via AudioComponentChain |
| Project item color labels | YES | YES | 16 colors (0-15) |
| Track item color labels | NO | NO | Not exposed in any API |
| Sequence markers | YES | YES | Full CRUD operations |
| Clip/ProjectItem markers | YES | YES | Full CRUD operations |
| Marker colors | YES | YES | 7 colors available |

---

## Key Version Information

- **Premiere Pro v25.6+**: UXP officially supported (released Dec 2025)
- **UXP Version**: v8.1 (bundled with Premiere v25.6)
- **ExtendScript**: Supported through September 2026
